summary: This is an email from an Assistant United States Attorney in the Southern District of New York requesting service of a subpoena to Expedia relating to travel by Ghislaine Maxwell. It demonstrates ongoing investigative efforts in the Maxwell case in early 2020.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: The subpoena relates to her travel records, indicating she is a central figure in the ongoing investigation.

events.title: Subpoena issued to Expedia
events.description: An Assistant United States Attorney requests service of a subpoena to Expedia for travel records related to Ghislaine Maxwell.

locations: 1 St. Andrew's Plaza, New York, NY 10007
keyFacts: A subpoena was issued to Expedia on January 24, 2020, for travel records related to Ghislaine Maxwell.
The request was made by an Assistant United States Attorney in the Southern District of New York.
The document shows active investigation into Maxwell's activities in early 2020, prior to her arrest in July 2020.
